A good winter is promised to German tour operators.
According to one study, the traffic of bookings for the following months increased significantly compared to the previous year - more than 30 percent for the winter season.
Despite the weak economic outlook, the Germans’ desire to travel, according to the study, did not slow down.
In winter season bookings, travel agencies recorded a 31 percent increase in traffic compared to the previous year, the German Travel Association (DRV) said on Monday in Berlin.
