EU and India double trade
Since the European Union and India are mutually leading trade partners, the agenda of the ninth summit was dominated by this topic, along with other, largely global problems.
Today, there will also be a French-Indian summit, where nuclear cooperation will be the main issue.
Although the European Union recognises that India is an emerging democratic power that should have a greater say in international affairs, the Member States have not yet managed to reach a common denominator whether to support New Delhi's permanent membership of the UN Security Council.
This issue was thus not pressed at the ninth summit in Marseille yesterday.
French President Nicolas Sarkozy, as President-in-Office of the Union, Commission President José Manuel Barroso and High Representative Javier Solana welcomed Indian Prime Minister Manmohan Singh, with whom they agreed to double trade in five years, i.e. increase trade turnover to hundreds of billions of euros.
Given that the exchange of goods increased from 25 billion to 55 billion between 2000 and 2007, this is not a very ambitious goal.
In this spirit, the twenty-six bilateral civil aviation agreements with India have been legally agreed, i.e. air traffic can also soar in the future.
India wants to sign a free trade agreement with the EU by the end of 2009.
Sarkozy promised to speed up the negotiations.
The aim is to balance that while the EU is India's number one trading partner, New Delhi is only in ninth place among the EU's partners.
The summit focused its attention on global affairs.
The situation in Afghanistan and Pakistan, as well as terrorism, has been condemned in all its forms on both sides and called for the UN conference to be convened.
They also called for the end of the Doha trade round, although both of them have a large part of the failure so far.
The EU has confirmed its commitment to its energy and climate programme to reduce emissions by at least 20 percent by 2020.
India agreed with this, as well as the fact that a global deal should be reached at the next climate conference and greenhouse gas production should be reduced by 50 percent by 2050.
I would also like to hinder the rise in food prices and support the convening of an international meeting to review the financial crisis.
Today, the Indian Prime Minister is going to the French capital, where he is about to do business at the bilateral meeting on the peaceful use of nuclear energy.
In Paris, they hope that French companies will be commissioned to build Indian nuclear reactors worth 20 billion euros.
According to the news agency, the agreement would be for 15 years.
More than 300 Italian publishers in Frankfurt
Italian publishers will be represented at the Frankfurt International Book Fair with a strong field.
More than 300 Italian publishing houses will be present at the 60th Buchmesse Fair, the most important international copyright meeting.
This year’s Frankfurt International Book Fair will feature 7,000 exhibitors from 101 countries, with a floor area of 171,790 square metres, where more than 403,000 books will be presented. The guest of honor will be Turkey.
At the opening ceremony of the Italian Pavilion, the Italian government will be represented by Francesco Maria Giro, Deputy State Secretary of the Ministry of Cultural Goods and Activities: Italy will occupy a 264 square metre exhibition area by setting up a single Italia Point.
The opening ceremony will be followed by a press conference in the "Room Struktur" room of Buchmesse's 5.0 pavilion, where there will also be an opportunity to present data, trends and prospects on the situation of Italian publishing.
According to the data, the proportion of foreign authors on the Italian publishing market is constantly decreasing, especially in the field of adult and youth publications.
The plane of billionaire Steve Fossett, who disappeared a year ago, was found.
They found the remains of the billionaire Steve Fossett's plane, who disappeared over the Nevada desert on September 3, 2007.
The wreckage was found on a 3,000 - metre - high plateau near Mammoth Lakes in the Sierra Nevada Mountains on the border between California and Nevada.
No human remains were found inside the aircraft.
John Anderson, the sheriff of Madera County, dismissed all remaining doubts: "After determining the position of the plane, we sent a team out, and now we can be sure it's the plane Steve Fossett flew on the day of his disappearance," he said at a press conference.
The sheriff also confirmed that no human remains were found in the plane or in the surrounding area.
The 63-year-old billionaire was declared dead in February.
The U.S. Transportation Safety Agency (NTSB) said that a few hours after the discovery of the wreckage, a commission of inquiry was asked to identify the plane and determine that it was indeed the Bellanca 8kcab that disappeared on September 3, 2007, the day Fossett left Yerington, Nevada, for a three-hour flight.
Yesterday, also in California, not far from the Nevada border, a couple found some of Fossett's personal belongings near his home in Mammoth Lakes.
Two I.D.s in Fosset's name issued by the Illinois Federal Aviation Administration, some cash and a sweater.
Fossett's search was given up a month after he disappeared.
The billionaire set up a number of peaks by which he wrote himself into history.
In 2002, on the sixth attempt, he first managed to fly around the earth with a balloon: two weeks of lonely flight.
Three years later, he went around the world by plane without landing.
Many of his records include flying over the Andes at a height of 15,445 meters, which he performed with a co-pilot.
